<li><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://intersci.ss.uci.edu/wiki/index.php/Maps_of_Time:_An_Introduction_to_Big_History"><b>Maps of Time</b> at InterSci Complexity wiki</a></li>
<li><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.ucpress.edu/books/pages/9249/9249.intro.html">Maps of Time: Introduction</a>. 2004. Introduction chapter from the book.</li>
<li><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.historycooperative.org/journals/jwh/14.4/christian.html">World History in Context</a>. 2003. Christian makes the case that human history is significant across all time scales.</li>
<li><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.fss.uu.nl/wetfil/96-97/big.htm">"The Case for Big History"</a>. 1991. An early essay.</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.communities.uva.nl/bighistory">Big History</a> Big History courses at the University of Amsterdam.</li>
<li><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.socionauki.ru/journal/seh_en/archive/2005_1/">Exploring the Horizons of Big History</a> - Special issue of the journal <a href="Social_Evolution_&_History" title="Social Evolution &amp; History">Social Evolution &amp; History</a> (Guest Editor Graeme Donald Snooks)</li>
<li><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://newbooksinhistory.com/?p=3121">Interview</a> with Fred Spier about Big History on New Books in History.</li>
<li><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.blurb.com/bookstore/detail/1235501">And Then There Was You...</a>. 2010. A children's book by Erika K.H. Gronek</li>
<li><a rel="nofollow" class="external autonumber" href="http://usm.maine.edu/lac/global/bighistory/">[2]</a> Big History, University of Southern Maine, Lewiston, Maine (USA).</li>
<li>Institute of Global Dynamic Systems. <a rel="nofollow" class="external autonumber" href="https://sites.google.com/site/institutegds/">[3]</a></li>
<li><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://science.time.com/2012/05/07/visualizing-the-anthropocene/">Visualizing the anthropocene</a> three minute video highlighting man's impact</li>
</ul>


